caption.p: Effect of S. chamaecyparissus and T. patula essential oils on the concentration of lipid peroxidation products (TBARS) (mean ± SD) within tissues of M. persicae ( A) and R. padi ( B). Values marked by different letters are significantly different at p < 0.05 (Tukey’s test). Statistics for two-way ANOVA: (A) treatment F 2,24 = 31.12, p < 0.001, time F 3,24 = 7.63, p < 0.001, treatment × time interaction F 6,24 = 4.55, p < 0.01; (B) treatment F 2,24 = 73.50, p < 0.001, time F 3,24 = 15.15, p < 0.001, treatment × time interaction F 6,24 = 9.56, p < 0.001.
